---

<SlideLayout title="SASS">
    <AgendaSection header="SASS" h3="Syntactically Awesome Style Sheets"/>
    <section>
        <p>CSS as it should be</p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <p>CSS as it will be</p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <Goal>
            <ol>
                <li>Understand why devs use SASS</li>
                <li>Be able to write SASS</li>
                <li>Know where to find more ressources</li>
            </ol>
        </Goal>
    </section>
    
    <AgendaSection header="Agenda">
        <section>
            <ul>
                <li>The week plan</li>
                <li>What is it?</li>
                <li>Why do we use it?</li>
                <li>How to install it?</li>
                <li>The syntax</li>
                <li>Componetizing</li>
                <li>A cool trick</li>
                <li>+3</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </AgendaSection>

    <AgendaSection header="The Week plan">
        <section>
            <h3>To many changes?</h3>
            <dl>
                <dt>Monday</dt>
                <dd>KEA 8:45 - 12:30</dd>
                <dt>Tuesday</dt>
                <dd>Teams 8:45 - 12:00</dd>
                <dt>Wednesday</dt>
                <dd>Tutors available</dd>
                <dt>Thursday</dt>
                <dd>KEA 12:45 - 16:00</dd>
                <dt>Friday</dt>
                <dd>Teams 8:45 - 12:45</dd>
            </dl>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>Tuesday setup</h3>
            <p>For those who want to</p>
            <ul>
                <li>We have 3 tutors in class</li>
                <li>They have agreed to be sparring partners</li>
                <li>One of them will setup a computer to the projector</li>
                <li>I'll find a microphone</li>
                <li>Speakers to be tested Monday</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>KEAPlan won't change</strong></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Exceptions</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>15/11 Tuesday, Guest Speaker</li>
                <li>25/11 Friday, Client Presentation</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </AgendaSection>

    <AgendaSection header="What is it">
    
        <section>
            <p>SASS is a CSS preprocessor</p>
            <p>We write SCSS/SASS and the preprocessor translates it into CSS</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>Two competing syntaxes</h3>
            <p>.scss</p>
            <p>.sass</p>
            <p>We'll be using .scss</p>
            <p><strong>so all our files will be called .scss in the end</strong></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <blockquote><p>I write style sheets by hand! I don’t need help! And I certainly don’t want to add extra complexity to my workflow. Go away!</p></blockquote>
            <cite> - Dan Cederholm
                <a href="http://alistapart.com/articles/why-sass">http://alistapart.com/articles/why-sass</a></cite>
        </section>
    </AgendaSection>
    
    <AgendaSection header="Why do we use it">
        <section>
            <p>Because CSS is missing stuff "we need"</p>
            <ul>
                <li><del>Variables</del></li>
                <li>Reusable blocks</li>
                <li>Conditionals</li>
                <li>Loops</li>
                <li>Functions</li>
                <li>Math (sorry)</li>
                <li>Minification</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>The good parts</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>It's (almost) just CSS</li>
                <li>We can use as little or as much as we like</li>
                <li>It's not that hard</li> 
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <blockquote><p>Once I started using Sass, I never once thought it was awkward or laborious—it just feels like CSS should feel. Once you try it, you’ll likely stick with it permanently</p></blockquote>
            <cite> - Dan Cederholm <a href="http://alistapart.com/articles/why-sass">http://alistapart.com/articles/why-sass</a></cite>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>The bad parts</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>It's a new thing to learn</li>
                <li>It doesn't work without the "preprocessor"</li>
                <li>It might not stick around</li>
                <li>It's not the only one</li>
                <li>SCSS vs SASS</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </AgendaSection>

    <AgendaSection header="How do we install it?">
        <section>
            <h2>One way <span class="fragment">(that we care about)</span></h2>
            <ol>
                <li><code>Vite</code></li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </AgendaSection>
